# Documented exceptions to the CI's Trivy scan (severity CRITICAL,HIGH).
# Applies only to the 6 Debian/Python-based services; the 3 Java services
# use an Alpine base image with an unrelated package set, so none of these
# CVE (Common Vulnerabilities and Exposures) IDs match there.
#
# Every entry below was verified against security-tracker.debian.org on
# 2026-07-07: Debian trixie has no fixed package version for any of them
# yet, and its own security team has already classified them as low
# priority (see notes per entry). This file documents an accepted risk,
# it does not silence an unreviewed one. Revisit when the base image
# (python:3.14.6-slim) picks up a trixie point release that includes
# these fixes.

# gzip, HIGH - no fixed version in trixie yet
CVE-2026-41992

# libacl1, HIGH - no fixed version in trixie yet
CVE-2026-54369

# ncurses family (libncursesw6, libtinfo6, ncurses-base, ncurses-bin), HIGH
# - no fixed version in trixie yet
CVE-2025-69720

# perl-base, CRITICAL - Debian: "postponed, minor issue, wait for
# regressions upstream sorted out"
CVE-2026-42496

# perl-base, CRITICAL - fixed only in Debian unstable (5.40.1-8), not
# backported to trixie yet
CVE-2026-8376

# perl-base, HIGH - Debian: "postponed, minor issue"
CVE-2026-42497

# perl-base, HIGH - no fixed version in trixie yet
CVE-2026-48962

# perl-base, HIGH - Debian: "postponed, minor issue"
CVE-2026-9538

# --- Alpine (3 Java services, eclipse-temurin:*-jre-alpine) ---
# Unlike the Debian entries above, these are NOT expected to stay
# unfixed long-term: Alpine 3.23 is actively supported and the fix
# already exists upstream (p11-kit 0.26.2-r0). The eclipse-temurin
# image just hasn't been rebuilt yet to pick it up (still on the
# 2026-06-22 build as of 2026-07-07). Jib cannot run "apk upgrade"
# during the image build (no RUN-equivalent step, by design), so
# there is no way to apply this patch ourselves without switching
# away from Jib. Remove this entry once
# `docker buildx imagetools inspect eclipse-temurin:17-jre-alpine`
# shows a newer build date than 2026-06-22.

# p11-kit / p11-kit-trust, HIGH - fix (0.26.2-r0) not yet in the
# pinned eclipse-temurin build; not used at runtime by this app
# (PKCS#11 hardware token middleware, no hardware tokens involved)
CVE-2026-2100
